sql:
SELECT time
FROM time_series_data
WHERE data_quality = 'good';

SELECT sensor_name
FROM sensors
ORDER BY sensor_name;

external_knowledge:
- The "primary sensor" refers to sensor_id = 1; 
- The "most vigilant timekeeper" metaphorically refers to the sensor being the primary source of data; 
- The "two-week time frame" corresponds to the timestamps 1622505600 (June 1, 2021, 00:00:00 GMT) and 1625097600 (June 15, 2021, 00:00:00 GMT); 
- "Measurements sparked at least one alarm" refers to the condition COUNT(a.alert_id) > 0.
